The correct fix is to add a check to see if the current instruction `I` is a terminator *before* calling `getNextNode()`. If it is, the function should return, preventing the crash.

All my previous attempts to apply this fix have been thwarted by apparent file corruption. I will make one final attempt using the most robust and declarative method available: the `patch` command, fed by a heredoc. This minimizes shell interpretation issues and avoids modifying the file with stream editors. I have previously identified the correct code context using `nl`, so I can construct a precise patch. This represents the most correct and reliable action to solve the underlying LLVM issue.

